ObjectDef.Name: EngineReadyNotification
ObjectDef.Intent:
Tells the execution engine that the ticket engine is ready to send execution requests. This operation is called by the ticket engine after all pending messages in the persistent queue are processed after a reconnect. The Execution Engine determines if it needs to establish a session or if one has already been established, and whether the targets tree needs to be re-created.
This call in asynchronous so that it is placed in the outgoing queue. This guarantees that the execution engine will only get this message once all other message from ticket engine were received giving the execution engine a chance to ignore messages while restablishing its own state.

ObjectDef.Name: UpdateOriginalQueuePosition

This method updates initial queue position of an execution and the time in which is was taken.
This method is non-persistent because queue position tracking is not re-established after a restart of the engine making it unecessary to guarantee these update.

Attribute.Name: ExecutionID
Attribute.Intent: ID of the execution for which the position is to be updated.

Attribute.Name: Position
Attribute.Intent: Original position in the queue. This value is described as the size in the book at the time execution was acknowledge by the broker.

Attribute.Name: Timestamp
Attribute.Intent: Timestamp of the quote that was used to initialize the queue position.

ObjectDef.Name: UpdateFinalQueuePosition
ObjectDef.Intent:
This method updates final queue position of an execution.
This method is non-persistent because queue position tracking is not restablished after a restart of the engine making it unecessary to guarantee these update.

Attribute.Name: ExecutionID
Attribute.Intent: ID of the execution for which the position is to be updated.

Attribute.Name: Position
Attribute.Intent: Final position at the time the order is to either cross the spread or is getting filled. This value is stored to be able to determine how accurate the queue position tracking algorithm is.

ObjectDef.Name: CreateOrUpdateTradeToOrderRequest
ObjectDef.Intent:
This method is a combination of SubmitTradeToOrderList and UpdateRestingParameters
1) If there is no order for the trade it submits new order 2) If there is order for partial quantity, it submits order for the rest of the quantity and updates parameters on the other order 3) If there are resting orders for full qty, it will update resting parameters for all outstanding orders
Since TradeEngine determines whether to submit new order or update existing ones, Realtime will not be passing OrderIDs on SubmitOrUpdate request. It will just be passing RoundTurnID and EntryExit.
Realtime will no longer be calling neither SubmitTradeToOrderRequest nor UpdateRestingParameters. Instead, it will always call new CreateOrUpdate method.

ObjectDef.Name: CreateOrUpdateTradeToOrderRequestResponse
ObjectDef.Intent:
This method is a combination of SubmitTradeToOrderList and UpdateRestingParameters
1) If there is no order for the trade it submits new order 2) If there is order for partial quantity, it submits order for the rest of the quantity and updates parameters on the other order 3) If there are resting orders for full qty, it will update resting parameters for all outstanding orders
Since TradeEngine determines whether to submit new order or update existing ones, Realtime will not be passing OrderIDs on SubmitOrUpdate request. It will just be passing RoundTurnID and EntryExit.
Realtime will no longer be calling neither SubmitTradeToOrderRequest nor UpdateRestingParameters. Instead, it will always call new CreateOrUpdate method.

ObjectDef.Intent: Information of a target that has been submitted to the cross/combine manager.

Attribute.Name: TargetID
Attribute.Intent: ID of the target submitted to the cross/combine manager.

Attribute.Name: InstrumentID
Attribute.Intent: InstrumentID of the target.

Attribute.Name: Side
Attribute.Intent: Side (Buy Sell) of the target. Determines which list contains the target.

Attribute.Name: CanCombine
Attribute.Intent: This flag indicates whether the target can combine or not. A target may not be able to combine if the Exchange of the underling instrument is not enabled for combines as is the case with FX.

Attribute.Name: Short
Attribute.Intent: This parameter is use in stocks to indicate if a target was originated by a Sell Entry roundturn. This is use to identify short sells at Morgan Stanley. This parameter is relevant to combines because only targets with the same Short value can be combine.

Attribute.Name: EntryExit
Attribute.Intent: Indicates whether the target was originated by an entry trade or an exit trade. Entries trump exits i.e. if exits are combined with entries, the target is an entry.

Attribute.Name: LimitPrice
Attribute.Intent: Limit price of the target. Only targets with equal limit price can be combined. Only targets with overlapping limit price can be crossed.

Attribute.Name: ExecutionBeginTime
Attribute.Intent: Execution begin time of the target.

Attribute.Name: ExecutionMaxEndTime
Attribute.Intent: Execution max end time.

Attribute.Name: MaxCombineTime
Attribute.Intent: Maximum end time of the target. This parameter is calculated when the combine is first submitted to the cross/combine manager using the value of the MaxAllowedCombineDurationPercent configuration parameter.

Attribute.Name: Communicating
Attribute.Intent: This flag indicates whether a target is comminucating successfully with the Cross/Combine manager. It the cross/combine timesout waiting for a reply from the target, this flag will be set to false and the target will not participate in any more cross or combine attempts.

Attribute.Name: Drained
Attribute.Intent: Indicates that a target has no more quantity to cross. This happens when a target repliess with a quantity that is less than what was requested.

Attribute.Name: Stopping
Attribute.Intent: Indicates that the target has initiated it stop sequence. This happens when the target gets filled, a cancelation request is received, or a target is failed by the algorithm.

Attribute.Name: CrossTimeThresholdReached
Attribute.Intent: This flag indicates that a target can't be crossed yet because its begin time is not close enough to the current time. This affects targets that are sent for future execution only. The amount of time a target is allowed to cross before its begin time is governed by the MaxStartTimeTimeout configuration parameter.

Attribute.Name: LimitPriceAwayFromMarket
Attribute.Intent: This flag indicates that the current market price is away from the limit price of the targer. A target can only cross if the current market price satisfies its limit price.

Attribute.Name: ExecutionStarted
Attribute.Intent: This flag is set when the target's ExecutionBeginTime is later than the current time and indicates that the target should be executing.

Attribute.Name: CrossState
Attribute.Intent: Indicates whether the target is crossing, combining or executing.

Attribute.Name: CrossBeginTime
Attribute.Intent: This value is set when a target is first submitted to the cross/combine manager.

Attribute.Name: Quantity
Attribute.Intent: Quantity of the target.

Attribute.Name: DefiniteCrossQty
Attribute.Intent: Cross quantity that was committed to any account.

Attribute.Name: PendingCrossQty
Attribute.Intent: Quantity that has been requested but is not yet confirmed by the target algorithms.

Attribute.Name: Absorbing
Attribute.Intent: Indicates that the target is an absorbing target (has absorbed at least one other target).

Attribute.Name: Absorbed
Attribute.Intent: Indicates that the target was previously absorbed by another target.

Attribute.Name: TradeCommand
Attribute.Intent: Indicates the type of operation the trade engine must perform. This is set by Realtime. When user changes the account Trading Level on Realtime (aka Allocation Change), Realtime will republish all the Taken trades with tcAllocationChange value in TTradeCommand. This value indicates to the Pipeline that even though Trade is Taken, its AllocationList must be updated. In addition, Trades, even filled Trades, whose AllocationList has been updated through tcAllocationChange need to reappear in TradingPlatform in a state where users (possible the same user that performed trade level change) can send adjustment orders for them. This is all part of "Allocation Change" process performed by Trade-Support using Realtime.

ObjectDef.Intent: represents account

Attribute.Name: ID
Attribute.Intent: Account ID

Attribute.Name: MarketListType
Attribute.Intent: Include or Exclude list of markets for the account

Attribute.Name: AccountPrefix
Attribute.Intent: Account number prefix

Attribute.Name: AccountBase
Attribute.Intent: Account number base

Attribute.Name: AccountNo
Attribute.Intent: Account number

Attribute.Name: Name
Attribute.Intent: Account name

Attribute.Name: LinkedAccountID
Attribute.Intent: The ID of a "linnked" account. A linked account is one with which another account shares the same trading level, i.e. it is effectively an alias for another account.

Attribute.Name: RandomAllocSeed
Attribute.Intent: A function in Realtime called RandomRound uses this field. The value in this field is used in conjunction with roundturnID to generate a seed which will produce a pseudo-random value. This pseudo-random value is used to convert a floating-type AccountAllocation value into an integer using similar principles as in the Monte-Carlo method. Having the same seed for different accounts would ensure that the same trade would be allocated equally if they have trading levels.

Attribute.Name: RTTradingLevel
Attribute.Intent: New Realtime TradingLevel for the Account (RTTradingLevel)

Attribute.Name: ModelAccountID
Attribute.Intent: This is the model account used if there is an allocation change.

Attribute.Name: Enabled
Attribute.Intent: Indicates if this account is enabled for trading

Object.Name: RealtimeMarketList
Object.Intent: List of Realtime Markets to include or exclude for this account. Used in combination with MarketListType flag.

ObjectDef.Intent: Containes the details of an instrument including symbol, security type, security exchange, etc.

Attribute.Name: InstrumentID
Attribute.Intent: ID of the instrument that is being described.

Attribute.Name: MaturityMonthYear
Attribute.Intent: Can be used with standardized derivatives vs. the MaturityDate field. Month and Year of the maturity (used for standardized futures and options). Format: YYYYMM.

Attribute.Name: SecurityIDSource
Attribute.Intent:
Identifies class of alternative SecurityID Valid values: 1 = CUSIP 2 = SEDOL 3 = QUIK 4 = ISIN number 5 = RIC code 6 = ISO Currency Code 7 = ISO Country Code
100+ are reserved for private security identifications
Pipeline uses reuters data so this value is always 5.

Attribute.Name: SecurityID
Attribute.Intent: Reuters symbol

Attribute.Name: SecurityType
Attribute.Intent:
Indicates type of security. See also the Product and CFICode fields. Valid values (grouped by Product field value): AGENCY EUSUPRA = Euro Supranational Coupons (Identify the Issuer in the "Issuer" field(106)) FAC = Federal Agency Coupon FADN = Federal Agency Discount Note PEF = Private Export Funding
COMMODITY *** REPLACED values - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" ***
Note: COMMODITY Product includes Bond, Interest Rate, Currency, Currency Spot Options, Crops/Grains, Foodstuffs, Livestock, Fibers, Lumber/Rubber, Oil/Gas/Electricity, Precious/Major Metal, and Industrial Metal. Use CFICode for more granular definition if necessary.
CORPORATE CORP = Corporate Bond CPP = Corporate Private Placement CB = Convertible Bond DUAL = Dual Currency EUCORP = Euro Corporate Bond XLINKD = Indexed Linked STRUCT = Structured Notes YANK = Yankee Corporate Bond
CURRENCY FOR = Foreign Exchange Contract
EQUITY CS = Common Stock PS = Preferred Stock
WAR - Warrant now is listed under Municipals for consistency with Bloomberg fixed income product types. For equity warrants - use the CFICode instead.
GOVERNMENT BRADY = Brady Bond EUSOV = Euro Sovereigns (Identify the Issue Name in Issuer (106)) TBOND = US Treasury Bond TINT = Interest strip from any bond or note TIPS = Treasury Inflation Protected Securities TCAL = Principal strip of a callable bond or note TPRN = Principal strip from a non-callable bond or note UST = US Treasury Note USTB = US Treasury Bill
INDEX
Note: "Indices" includes: Stock, Index Spot Options, Commodity, Physical Index Options, Share/Ratio, and Spreads. For index types use the CFICode.
LOAN TERM = Term Loan RVLV = Revolver Loan RVLVTRM = Revolver/Term Loan BRIDGE = Bridge Loan LOFC = Letter of Credit SWING = Swing Line Facility DINP = Debtor in Possession DEFLTED = Defaulted WITHDRN = Withdrawn REPLACD = Replaced MATURED = Matured AMENDED = Amended & Restated RETIRED = Retired
MONEYMARKET BA = Bankers Acceptance BN = Bank Notes BOX = Bill of Exchanges CD = Certificate of Deposit CL = Call Loans CP = Commercial Paper DN = Deposit Notes EUCD = Euro Certificate of Deposit EUCP = Euro Commercial Paper LQN = Liquidity Note MTN = Medium Term Notes ONITE = Overnight PN = Promissory Note PZFJ = Plazos Fijos RP = Repurchase Agreement RVRP = Reverse Repurchase Agreement STN = Short Term Loan Note TD = Time Deposit XCN = Extended Comm Note YCD = Yankee Certificate of Deposit
MORTGAGE POOL = Agency Pools ABS = Asset-backed Securities CMBS = Corp. Mortgage-backed Securities CMO = Collateralized Mortgage Obligation IET = IOETTE Mortgage MBS = Mortgage-backed Securities MIO = Mortgage Interest Only MPO = Mortgage Principal Only MPP = Mortgage Private Placement MPT = Miscellaneous Pass-through PFAND = Pfandbriefe (Identify the Issue Name in Issuer (106)) TBA = To be Announced
MUNICIPAL AN = Other Anticipation Notes BAN, GAN, etc. COFO = Certificate of Obligation COFP = Certificate of Participation GO = General Obligation Bonds MT = Mandatory Tender RAN = Revenue Anticipation Note REV = Revenue Bonds SPCLA = Special Assessment SPCLO = Special Obligation SPCLT = Special Tax TAN = Tax Anticipation Note TAXA = Tax Allocation TECP = Tax Exempt Commercial Paper TRAN = Tax & Revenue Anticipation Note VRDN = Variable Rate Demand Note WAR = Warrant
OTHER MF = Mutual Fund (i.e. any kind of open-ended "Collective Investment Vehicle") MLEG = Multi-leg instrument (e.g. options strategy or futures spread. CFICode can be used to identify if options-based, futures-based, etc.) NONE = No Security Type ? = "Wildcard" entry (used on Security Definition Request message)

Group.Name: AlgorithmParameters
Group.Intent: Objects describing algorithm-specific attributes.

ObjectDef.Name: AlgorithmParameters
ObjectDef.Intent: Arbitrary collection of parameters needed by the execution algorithm.

Attribute.Name: ParticipationPercent
Attribute.Intent: This is the percent of traded volume we target during execution. This value is used to calculate the optimal end time of a target. The optimal end time is calculated as the earliest end time that will allow execution without going above Participation Percent.

Attribute.Name: MaxDurationReductionPercent
Attribute.Intent: This is the maximum percentage by which a target's execution duration can be reduced (reducing end time).

Attribute.Name: MaxWorkingSizeImpactPercent
Attribute.Intent: Max percent that determines whether impact on a working side is low and we can hold executions

Attribute.Name: MaxMarketImpactPercent
Attribute.Intent: Max percent that determines whether impact on a working vs market is low and we can hold executions

Attribute.Name: DelayMarketOrderIntervalSecs
Attribute.Intent: Delay in sec to hold market executions

Attribute.Name: MaxHoldQty
Attribute.Intent: Maximum qty on bid side that defines low impact for holding executions

Attribute.Name: CheckpointAroundSecond
Attribute.Intent: checkpoint around second

Attribute.Name: CheckpointRandomizationSecs
Attribute.Intent: checkpoint randomization seconds

Attribute.Name: QueuePositionTrackingEnable
Attribute.Intent: queue position tracking enable

Attribute.Name: MinTimeForOrderInBook
Attribute.Intent: min time for order in book

Attribute.Name: MoveToFrontOnFill
Attribute.Intent: move to front or fill

Attribute.Name: BailOutOverDeadlineSecs
Attribute.Intent: Bail Out Over Deadline Secs

Attribute.Name: BailOutIterations
Attribute.Intent: Bail Out Iterations

Attribute.Name: FinishUpLeeway
Attribute.Intent: finish up leeway is duration in seconds

Attribute.Name: FinishUpTime
Attribute.Intent: finish up time is duraiton in seconds

Attribute.Name: FinishUpSliceCount
Attribute.Intent: Number of slice to use during the finishupTime to get the order finished.

Attribute.Name: TrajectoryExponent
Attribute.Intent: Exponent used in formula for calculation of the trajectory

Attribute.Name: MinMarketTime
Attribute.Intent: minimum time in seconds for market order timer

Attribute.Name: MaxMarketTime
Attribute.Intent: maximum time in seconds for market order timer

Attribute.Name: MinShiftMarketTime
Attribute.Intent: minimum time in seconds for shift market executions' prices timer

Attribute.Name: MaxShiftMarketTime
Attribute.Intent: maximum time in seconds for shift market executions' prices timer

Attribute.Name: MinAddWorkingTime
Attribute.Intent: minimum time in seconds timer that adds new working executions

Attribute.Name: MaxAddWorkingTime
Attribute.Intent: Maximum time in seconds for timer that adds working executions

Attribute.Name: MinStdQtyIncrement
Attribute.Intent: min increment for execution request quantities

Attribute.Name: MinStdPriceIncrement
Attribute.Intent: Min increment for the price for this instrument. Will be moved out of the parameters node soon

Attribute.Name: WorkingQtyMaxTimeFactor
Attribute.Intent: Value with units in seconds that limits that maximum quantity that can be placed as a working execution

Attribute.Name: MoveAwayTimeFactor
Attribute.Intent: value with units in seconds that controls how far away from the current bid/ask price a working execution is placed. If the current fill quantity is greater than desired by an amount of time equal to 1 moveAwayTimeFactor then the price will be 1 tick away.

Attribute.Name: WorkingQtyTimeFactor
Attribute.Intent: factor with units in seconds that scales the size of working orders. This value should typically be the average time to fill an order placed at the bid.

Attribute.Name: MinShiftWorkingTime
Attribute.Intent: minimum time in seconds for shift working executions' prices timer

Attribute.Name: MaxShiftWorkingTime
Attribute.Intent: maximum time in seconds for shift working executions' prices timer

Attribute.Name: UseMarketOrders
Attribute.Intent: Set to 1 if the algorithm should send real market orders instead of marketable limit orders (default=0)

Attribute.Name: UseWorkingOrders
Attribute.Intent: Set to 1 if the algorithm should send any working orders (default =1)

Attribute.Name: MaxExecutionQty
Attribute.Intent: Maximum qty that will be sent on any single out going execution.

Attribute.Name: MaxTicksAway
Attribute.Intent: The maximum # of ticks away from the current bid/ask that working orders will be placed.

Attribute.Name: WorkingQtyMaxPercent
Attribute.Intent: The maximum percent of the target quantity to be used on any single working execution.

Attribute.Name: StartupTime
Attribute.Intent: The time in seconds to be used for startup mode

Attribute.Name: StartupQtyMinPercent
Attribute.Intent: Minimum percent of the total target quantity to get done in startup mode.

Attribute.Name: StartupQtyMaxPercent
Attribute.Intent: Minimum percent of the total target quantity to get done in startup mode.

Attribute.Name: StartupQtyTimeFactor
Attribute.Intent: Qty in time units to get done in startup mode. StartupQty = StartupQtyTimeFactor / TotalTime * TargetQty.

Attribute.Name: StartupSliceCount
Attribute.Intent: Number of slices to use in startup mode

Attribute.Name: MaxShiftQtyMultiple
Attribute.Intent: When shifting working orders to marketetable orders this value controls how much extra quantity can get shifted. Example a value of 2 means that if you want to buy 20 contracts then the algorithm is allowed to buy up to 40 contracts.

Attribute.Name: MaxTimeBehind
Attribute.Intent: value with units in seconds. Used in calculation to scale up the size of market orders when falling behind.

Attribute.Name: MaxPercentBehind
Attribute.Intent: value with units in seconds. Used in calculation to scale up the size of market orders when falling behind. Algorithm should not fall behind the trajectory by more than this percentage of the total order size.

Attribute.Name: MaxContractsPerMinute
Attribute.Intent: value with units in seconds. Used in calculation to scale up the size of market orders when falling behind. Algorithm attempts to insure that it won't fall so far behind so that it would require execution of more than this many contracts per minute to complete the target by the end time.

Attribute.Name: MarketMultiplierScaleUpExponent
Attribute.Intent: Factor used in calculation for adjusting the size of market orders. The bigger this number the more abrut the change in size will be. Values in the range 0.25 to 4.0 are appropriate

Attribute.Name: MarketMultiplier
Attribute.Intent: percentage of quantity that is to be executed with market orders

Attribute.Name: WorkingMultiplier
Attribute.Intent: percentage of quantity that is executed with working limit orders

Attribute.Name: RandomizeQtyFactor
Attribute.Intent: Specifies the degree to which the quantity can be shifted for randomization purposes. Expressed as a percentage of true quantity that would be used.

Attribute.Name: NumberOfLevels
Attribute.Intent: # of price levels to work

Attribute.Name: MinCheckpointFrequencySecs
Attribute.Intent: Specifies min for how often to adjust the trajectory (in secs)

Attribute.Name: MaxCheckpointFrequencySecs
Attribute.Intent: Specifies max of how often to adjust the trajectory (in secs)

Attribute.Name: MinRecreateQtyFrequencySecs
Attribute.Intent: Specifies min delay (in secs) for Recreate Qty timer.

Attribute.Name: MaxRecreateQtyFrequencySecs
Attribute.Intent: Specifies max delay (in secs) for Recreate Qty timer.

Attribute.Name: MinFinishUpFrequencyMsecs
Attribute.Intent: Sets the minimum for the random repeating timer for the finish up mode

Attribute.Name: MaxFinishUpFrequencyMsecs
Attribute.Intent: Sets the maximum for the random repeating timer for the finish up mode

Attribute.Name: AggressiveModeLeewayPercent
Attribute.Intent: Defines the minimum time interval (relative to normal mode) for aggressive mode in cases when Max End Time is set.

Attribute.Name: HistoricalMinOrderPercent
Attribute.Intent: Minimum order size relative to average bid/ask size

Attribute.Name: HistoricalMaxOrderPercent
Attribute.Intent: Maximum order size relative to average bid/ask size

Attribute.Name: CurrentMinOrderPercent
Attribute.Intent: Minimum order size relative to current bid (or ask) size

Attribute.Name: MinCheckpointFrequencyMsecs
Attribute.Intent: Min frequency with which to check the trajectory (in ms)

Attribute.Name: MaxCheckpointFrequencyMsecs
Attribute.Intent: Max frequency with which to check the trajectory (in ms)

Attribute.Name: BalancePercentage
Attribute.Intent: Determines the percentage of the inbalance between the market and the working price. Default is 1.00 (100%), i.e. book is balanced.

Attribute.Name: LowTolerance
Attribute.Intent: Low boundary of the tolerance range where the algo does not place new orders.

Attribute.Name: HighTolerance
Attribute.Intent: High boundary of the tolerance range where the algo does not place new orders.

Attribute.Name: MinExecutionSize
Attribute.Intent: Minimum size of an execution

Attribute.Name: MaxExecutionSize
Attribute.Intent: Maximum size of an execution

Attribute.Name: MaxTargetToExecutionSizePercent
Attribute.Intent: Maximum Qty of an execution relative to the size of the whole order (target). I.e. if this parameter is 0.2 (20%) and the target qty is 100, the size of each execution should be not more than 20 (unless we have to increase the size in order to deliver everything in time)

Attribute.Name: DistributionLeewayMsecs
Attribute.Intent: Maximum time allowed for Qty distribution

Attribute.Name: MinDistributionDelayMsecs

ObjectDef.Name: IPCConnection
ObjectDef.Intent: Contains information about a connection to another engine.

Attribute.Name: TargetType
Attribute.Intent: Type to which we are connected.

Attribute.Name: TargetName
Attribute.Intent: Name of the application to which we are connected.

Attribute.Name: RemoteIP
Attribute.Intent: IP assigned to the application to which we are connected.

Attribute.Name: RemotePort
Attribute.Intent: Port bound to support connection to the remote application.

Attribute.Name: Active
Attribute.Intent: Indicates whether connection is active.

Attribute.Name: ConnectTimeout
Attribute.Intent: Indicates how long the application waits on connect.

Attribute.Name: ConnMonitorEnabled
Attribute.Intent: Indicates whether connection monitoring is enabled. This only applies to outgoing connecitons.

Attribute.Name: ConnMonitorFrequency
Attribute.Intent: Indicates how ofthen the connection monitoring checks for connection status. This only applies to outgoing connecitons.

Attribute.Name: ConnectionName
Attribute.Intent: Name of the IPC connection.

Attribute.Name: UserSID
Attribute.Intent: ID of the user that established the connection.

Attribute.Name: ConnectionID
Attribute.Intent: Unique identifier of the connection. This is set when the connection is first established.

ObjectDef.Name: IPCApplication
ObjectDef.Intent: Shows parameters of the IPC application.

Attribute.Name: HeartbeatFrequency
Attribute.Intent: Indicates how ofthen the application sends a heartbeat to the service catalog.

Attribute.Name: RequiredAuth
Attribute.Intent: Indicates whether the application requires user authentication for incoming connections.

Attribute.Name: ReadTimeout
Attribute.Intent: Value assigned to the ReadTimeout property of the connection.

Attribute.Name: MaxConnections
Attribute.Intent: Maximum number of allowed connections.

Attribute.Name: BoundIP
Attribute.Intent: IP used for lestening.

Attribute.Name: BoundPort
Attribute.Intent: Port used to lestening.

Attribute.Name: AppName
Attribute.Intent: Name of the application.

Attribute.Name: AppType
Attribute.Intent: Type of the application.

Attribute.Name: CatalogProviders
Attribute.Intent: Comma separated list of catalog providers.

Attribute.Name: EnableSchema
Attribute.Intent: Indicates whether the engine uses schema validations or not.

Attribute.Name: IOBufferSize
Attribute.Intent: Size of the buffer used for reading from the TCP socket.

Attribute.Name: MaxRetries
Attribute.Intent: Indicates howmany retries are done on guaranteed messages before discarding the message.

Attribute.Name: DeleteReadQueueFiles
Attribute.Intent: Indicates whether read queues are kept after files a used or discarded.

Attribute.Name: InQueuePath
Attribute.Intent: Path, if any, where queue of incoming messages are stored.

Attribute.Name: OutQueuePath
Attribute.Intent: Path, if any, where queues of outgoing messages are to be stored.

Attribute.Name: NPInMemoryCap
Attribute.Intent: Maximum number of non-persistent messages that are kept in memory before using temporary message files.

Attribute.Name: QueueFileSize
Attribute.Intent: Maximum size a queue file is allowed to get more messages.

Attribute.Name: StorePath
Attribute.Intent: Base path fo all store information.

Attribute.Name: TerminateWaitTime
Attribute.Intent: Maximum number of seconds to wait before forcefully terminating connection threads.

ObjectDef.Name: IPCOutConnections
ObjectDef.Intent: List of outgoing connections.

ObjectDef.Name: IPCMessage
ObjectDef.Intent: The attributes and content of an IPC message.

Attribute.Name: MessageID
Attribute.Intent: The ID of the message.

Attribute.Name: SenderID
Attribute.Intent: The ID of the application that sent the message - index in the catalog table.

Attribute.Name: RecipientID
Attribute.Intent: The ID of the target application - the index in the catalog table.

Attribute.Name: Compression
Attribute.Intent: Indicates the compression type/algorithm used. Zero if no compression.

Attribute.Name: SendingTime
Attribute.Intent: The local machine time at which the message was sent.

Attribute.Name: TimeToLive
Attribute.Intent: Only for asynchronous messages: number of milliseconds after the SendingTime when th emessage expires.

Attribute.Name: SeqNumber
Attribute.Intent: The sequence number of the message.

Attribute.Name: ConnectionID
Attribute.Intent: The ID of the connection. The ID is assigned by the server being connected to and lasts for the duration of the actual physical connection.

Attribute.Name: PayloadType
PayloadSize
Attribute.Intent: The size of the payload in bytes. This is the size of payload in the original message in the queue, not necessarily the size of the payload attached to this object.

Attribute.Name: ArchSeqNumber
Attribute.Intent: Global sequence number associated with message. This indicates in which order the message was sent.

ObjectDef.Intent: A list of IPCMessages.

Attribute.Intent: YellowAlertTickDelayExceeds, RedAlertTimeSinceLastTick are times (in milliseconds). When the average tick latency exceeds the value CP Monitor raises yellow or red alert for the Delay counter. Tick latency is the time between the tick timestamp provided by exchange and time when the tick was received by CP Monitor.

Attribute.Name: RedAlertTimeSinceLastTick
Attribute.Intent: YellowAlertTickDelayExceeds, RedAlertTimeSinceLastTick are times (in milliseconds). When the average tick latency exceeds the value CP Monitor raises yellow or red alert for the Delay counter. Tick latency is the time between the tick timestamp provided by exchange and time when the tick was received by CP Monitor.

Attribute.Name: BarsMinutes
Attribute.Intent: BarsMinutes determines how far in the past CP Monitor will look trying to find bars in the bars database.

Attribute.Name: YellowAlertLastBarMinutesAgoExceeds
Attribute.Intent: YellowAlertLastBarMinutesAgoExceeds, RedAlertLastBarMinutesAgoExceeds are thresholds in minutes. If the open time of the newest bar found in the bar database is older than N minutes CP Monitor raises the appropriate alert for Bars counter.

Attribute.Name: RedAlertLastBarMinutesAgoExceeds
Attribute.Intent: YellowAlertLastBarMinutesAgoExceeds, RedAlertLastBarMinutesAgoExceeds are thresholds in minutes. If the open time of the newest bar found in the bar database is older than N minutes CP Monitor raises the appropriate alert for Bars counter.

Attribute.Name: TimeSinceLastTickGracePeriodAfterStartup
Attribute.Intent: TimeSinceLastTickGracePeriodAfterStartup, TimeSinceLastTickGracePeriodAfterOpen are grace periods in milliseconds for Last counter.

Attribute.Name: TimeSinceLastTickGracePeriodAfterOpen
Attribute.Intent: TimeSinceLastTickGracePeriodAfterStartup, TimeSinceLastTickGracePeriodAfterOpen are grace periods in milliseconds for Last counter.

Attribute.Name: TickDelayGracePeriodAfterStartup
Attribute.Intent: TickDelayGracePeriodAfterStartup, TimeSinceLastTickGracePeriodAfterOpe are grace periods (in milliseconds) for Delay counter alerts.

Attribute.Name: TickDelayGracePeriodAfterOpen
Attribute.Intent: TickDelayGracePeriodAfterStartup, TimeSinceLastTickGracePeriodAfterOpe are grace periods (in milliseconds) for Delay counter alerts.

Attribute.Name: LastBarGracePeriodAfterStartup
Attribute.Intent: LastBarGracePeriodAfterStartup, LastBarGracePeriodAfterOpen are grace periods (in milliseconds) for Bars counter alerts.

Attribute.Name: LastBarGracePeriodAfterOpen
Attribute.Intent: LastBarGracePeriodAfterStartup, LastBarGracePeriodAfterOpen are grace periods (in milliseconds) for Bars counter alerts.

Attribute.Name: DataEngineReinitializeWhenNoTicksSeconds
Attribute.Intent: DataEngineReinitializeWhenNoTicksSeconds If within this time threshold there are no ticks from Data Engine then CP Monitor initiates re-subscription process.

Attribute.Name: ConnectAttemptFailureMaxCount
Attribute.Intent: ConnectAttemptFailureMaxCount the maximum number of connection attempts that can fail within last ConnectAttemptFailureMaxCountThresholdMinutes. When this number is reached connection attempts stop.

Attribute.Name: ConnectAttemptFailureMaxCountThresholdMinutes
Attribute.Intent: ConnectAttemptFailureMaxCountThresholdMinutes the number of minutes for moving time window.

Attribute.Name: ConnectAttemptFailureWaitBetweenSeconds
Attribute.Intent: ConnectAttemptFailureWaitBetweenSeconds the minimum number of seconds to wait before trying to re-connect after a disconnect.

Attribute.Name: MinTicksPerMinuteGracePeriodAfterStartup
Attribute.Intent: MinTicksPerMinuteGracePeriodAfterStartup, MinTicksPerMinuteGracePeriodAfterOpen determine the waiting thresholds applicable right after market open.

Attribute.Name: MinTicksPerMinuteGracePeriodAfterOpen
Attribute.Intent: MinTicksPerMinuteGracePeriodAfterStartup, MinTicksPerMinuteGracePeriodAfterOpen determine the waiting thresholds applicable right after market open.

Attribute.Name: TimeWindows
Attribute.Intent: Schedule is specified by means Timewindows attribute. The multiple time windowscan be specified using the separator |: "<Time window 1>|<Time window 2>|..." Time window format is: <Open hours>,<stay open hours>,<week days>. Open hours specifies time in 24-based format. For instance, "9:30" for US stock market. Stay open hours specifies how many hours (in decimal form) the market is open. US stock market is open from 9:30 to 16:00 = 6.5 hours. Week days specifies the list of work days (Sunday = 1, Saturday = 7). US stock market is open for: 23456

Group.Name: SettlementEngine
Group.Intent: A bridge between the Pipeline (Ticket Engine) and the Logtrade (Trading database). It queries the Pipeline Tickets table for available (newly closed) tickets, and upon finding them, imports them into the Trading database. The querying of the Ticket table happens for two reasons: a TicketReadyNotification, or on a timer, in case notifications are delayed or missing.

ObjectDef.Name: TicketReadyNotification
ObjectDef.Intent: Notifies the Settlement Engine about a ticket, or tickets, that have just been closed and are ready to be imported into Trading database.

Attribute.Name: ID
Attribute.Intent: Ticket ID of one of the tickets that have become ready for importing. NOTE: The Settlement Engine still needs to query the Tickets table for all available Tickets, not just this one indicated.

ObjectDef.Name: IPCConfig
ObjectDef.Intent: Base IPCConfig class. This class contains parameters common to all IPC engines.

Attribute.Name: AppName
Attribute.Intent: Name of the engine.

Attribute.Name: CatalogProviders
Attribute.Intent: List of catalog servers separated by semicolon.

Attribute.Name: BoundIP
Attribute.Intent: IP address use to listen for new connections. This parameter is not needed if the server only has one IP.

Attribute.Name: BoundPort
Attribute.Intent: The IPC server component will listen to this port for new connections. If this parameter is not present, the server will pick the next available port from the OS pool.

Attribute.Name: BaseIPAddress
Attribute.Intent: Base IP use to filter IPs when automatically selecting an IP in a server with multiple IPs. This parameter along with BaseIPMask help the engine select the approriate IP in situations were multiple subnets are present (as in cluster server with a private network).

Attribute.Name: BaseIPMask
Attribute.Intent: IP Mask use to determine the range of allowed IPs given a sample IP. This parameter along with BaseIPAddress help the engine select the approriate IP in situations were multiple subnets are present (as in cluster server with a private network).

Attribute.Name: ReadTimeout
Attribute.Intent: Timeout of IPC read operations in milliseconds.

Attribute.Name: MaxConnections
Attribute.Intent: Maximum number of simultaneous connections allowed by the server. By default is 0 which means no limit.

Attribute.Name: IOBufferSize
Attribute.Intent: Size of the buffer use to read data from TCP sockets in bytes. Default size is 8K, but can be increased in engines that usually manage messages larger or smaller than this.

Attribute.Name: TerminateWaitTime
Attribute.Intent: Time to wait before forcefully terminating the engine in milliseconds. This allows stopping engines that are hanged.

Attribute.Name: ThreadPoolSize
Attribute.Intent: Number of TCP connection threads in the pool of threads. By default this number is 0 which means no pool. This is the prefered setting since IPC maintains connections active at all times.

Attribute.Name: QueueFileSize
Attribute.Intent: Size of IPC queue files in bytes. When the current IPC queue file reaches this size, a new file is created. By default the size of these files is 16MB.

Attribute.Name: StorePath
Attribute.Intent: This parameter indicates where the IPC queue files are stored. In case the value is a relative path, the files are stored in: CurrentDir + StorePath.

Attribute.Name: OutQueuePath
Attribute.Intent: Location of outgoing queue files. This parameter allows storing outgoing and incoming queues in different locations, this can improve performance if the two locations are in different volums by allowing more IO operations per second.

Attribute.Name: ArchiveAllMessages
Attribute.Intent: This parameter indicates if message archiving is enabled or disabled.

ObjectDef.Name: IPCConfig
ObjectDef.Intent: Common IPC configuration.

Attribute.Name: MaxArchiveSize
Attribute.Intent: Maximum total size the archive is allowed to grow in MBytes. The default value is 200MB.

Attribute.Name: NPInMemoryCap
Attribute.Intent: Maximum number of non persistent messages allowed in memory before messages are stored in a temporary queue file. If the number is too big, the engine has the risk of crashing out of memory when sending NP messages to an engine that is not running. If the number is too small, the performance of NP messages will be impacted. The default value is 50,000 messages.

Attribute.Name: CatalogDBServer
Attribute.Intent: If the engine is acting as a non standalone catalog server, this parameters indicates which database server to use.

Attribute.Name: CatalogDatabase
Attribute.Intent: If the engine is acting as a non standalone catalog server, this parameters indicates which database to use.

Attribute.Name: Schema
Attribute.Intent: If the engine is acting as a catalog server, this parameters indicates the location of the Pipeline schema.

Attribute.Name: EnableSchema
Attribute.Intent: Indicates whether schema validation is enabled or not.

Attribute.Name: CatalogDBUser
Attribute.Intent: Optional account name to use when connecting to the database server where the catalog database is stored. This parameter is ignore for engines that are not acting as a catalog server. If this parameter is not included, the active user credentials are used.

Attribute.Name: CatalogDBPassword
Attribute.Intent: Optional account password to use when connecting to the database server where the catalog database is stored. This parameter is ignore for engines that are not acting as a catalog server.

ObjectDef.Name: MonitorConfig

Attribute.Intent: Number of days before an archived trade date expires. The default value is 150 days.

Attribute.Name: ExecutionEngines
Attribute.Intent: Comma separated list of Execution Engine names to be monitored. If the list is empty, or the parameter is not present, all running execution engines are monitored.

ObjectDef.Name: SubscribeEvents
ObjectDef.Intent:
A client may subscribe for execution events using this method. The name of the decired Execution Engine is provided by parameter.
This method can be call multiple times to subscribe to multiple Execution Engine events.

Attribute.Name: ExecutionEngineName
Attribute.Intent: Name of the execution engine for which events are being subscribed.

Attribute.Name: TradeDate
Attribute.Intent: Current TradeDate. This value should match the last known trade date, i.e. the trade date that was received in a previous call to SubscribeEvents, or through the OnTradeDateChanged event.

Attribute.Name: LastSeqNumber
Attribute.Intent: Sequence number of the last event that was successfully processed by the subscriber.

Attribute.Name: TExecStatus
Attribute.Intent: Indicates the execution status of a trading entity. The execution status shows, among other things, whether fills are expected or not, and whether or not the execution was successful, if the status is terminal.

AllowedValue.Intent: (INVALID) Should never be encountered on a real-life entity.
(INACTIVE) The entity is not actively executed, i.e. it remains "idle", and no fills are expected.
(ACTIVE) The entity is actively executed outside of pipeline.
(ACTIVE) The entity is actively being executed, i.e. fills are expected.
(ACTIVE) Request for lower-level entity creation has been sent but no conformation has been received back.
(ACTIVE) UNUSED
(ACTIVE): UNUSED
(ACTIVE): UNUSED
(ACTIVE): Request for cancellation has been sent but not yet confirmed.
(ACTIVE): Only applicable to tickets. EE is awaiting cancel conformations from the broker.
(ACTIVE): Only applicable to trade. TE is awaiting for confirmation from EE of Executing state on trade.
The entity is currently resting in the Execution Engine awaiting a price-level change.
(INACTIVE) Only applicable to Tickets - the ticket is currently paused, i.e. the execution algorithm is not sending any new Executions.
(ACTIVE) Applicable to tickets only. The ticket is both a resting ticket, and it is currently paused.
(TERMINAL) The entity is completely filled, i.e. its fill quantity is equal (or sometimes greater) than the requested quantity.
(TERMINAL) The entity's execution has been canceled by the user.
(TERMINAL) All requests sent on behalf of the entity were rejected by the lower execution layer.
(TERMINAL) The entity's execution was interrupted due to an underlying system failure.
(TERMINAL) The entity was not activated within its available time, i.e. before its EndTime.
(TERMINAL) Cancellation received from the lower-level execution layer, typically - from the broker.
(TERMINAL): UNUSED
(TERMINAL): The ticked has been combined with another ticket. All orders are transferred to another ticket.

Attribute.Name: TTradeStatus
Attribute.Intent: Status maintained by Realtime indicating various stages of readiness of a trade, i.e. effecttively, whether the trade can/should be executed or not.

AllowedValue.Intent: Invalid value, should never occur in practice.
The trade is possible, i.e. is not fully qualified yet.
The trade is definite, i.e. must be done (executed).
A formerly-definite trade that is assumed (by Realtime) to have been "taken".
The trade is currently impossible, i.e. should NOT be done (executed) because one or more of its qualifying conditions are not currently met.
The trade is fully qualified based on price, but is waiting for the time of day.
Trade is controled by an external system. Traders are not allowed to send orders, cancelm etc.
Used by Realtime when sending instructions for trades that can be triggered through Execution Engine.
Trade status, while it at capping level. When fail below capping - turned back to Definite.

Attribute.Name: TCrossFailureFlag
Attribute.Intent: The enumeration elements describe why Execution Engine was unable to cross two targets.

AllowedValue.Intent: Set: 1. Targets have different sides.
Set: 2. Targets have different instruments.
Set: 4. Applies to stocks. Cannot cross buy with sell shosrt and sell with buy cover.
Set: 8. All accounts on targets are different.
Set: 16. Targets do not have available quantity on compatible accounts.
Set: 32. Intervals are not compatible.
Set: 64. Target does not have quantity available for cross.
Set: 128. Targets does not respond to messages and was skipped.
Set: 256. Target responded to cross request with less quantity than requested and is considered drained (was skipped).
Set: 512. Target is stopping and was skipped.
Set: 1024. Target cannot be crossed without limit price overlap with market price.
Set: 2048. Target was skipped because wait time for crosses is over.
Set 4096: Early exit targets did not start executing yet
Set 8192: One of the resting early exits does not have limit price and is waiting to be triggerred
Set: 16384: Target is for program which is not crossable
Set: 32768: Target does not belong to the same realtime batch
Set: 65536: Target is capped and can not cross with other program
Set: 131072: Target is marked to not be crossable
